SIMPLE: electroplating
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: electroplating
<hw>e*lec"tro*pla`ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The art or
process of depositing a coating (commonly) of silver, gold, or nickel on
an inferior metal, by means of an electric current. The metal to be
deposited on an article is usually used as the anode and the article to
be plated as the cathode, in an electrolyte solution in which the
plating metal is the cation. The process is conducted in a tank called
an <ecol><b>electroplating bath</b></ecol>, which holds the electrolyte
solution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electropoion fluid</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Electropoion</ent>⟦br⟧
